qas.question: Along with South Dakota, what state rejected a death penalty abolition bill in 2010?
Since 1976, how many prisoners has Nevada executed?
Since 1976, in what year was a prisoner executed in Wyoming?
Along with North Dakota, what state rejected a death penalty abolition bill in 2010?
Since 1976, in what year was a prisoner freed in Wyoming?

context: In 2010, bills to abolish the death penalty in <a0_0><b5_0>Kansas<b5_0/><a0_0/> and in South Dakota (which had a de facto moratorium at the time) were rejected. Idaho ended its de facto moratorium, during which only one volunteer had been executed, on November 18, 2011 by executing <a1_0><b6_0>Paul Ezra Rhoades<b6_0/><a1_0/>; South Dakota executed <a2_0><b7_0>Donald Moeller<b7_0/><a2_0/> on October 30, 2012, ending a de facto moratorium during which only two volunteers had been executed. Of the <a3_0>12<a3_0/> prisoners whom Nevada has executed since 1976, 11 waived their rights to appeal. Kentucky and Montana have executed two prisoners against their will (KY: 1997 and 1999, MT: 1995 and 1998) and one volunteer, respectively (KY: 2008, MT: 2006). Colorado (in 1997) and Wyoming (in <a4_0><b8_0>1992<b8_0/><a4_0/>) have executed only one prisoner, respectively.
